doesn't already exist, and warns you if it does.
This is done by associating to each document a set of

identify a document. If two documents share a blocking key, theyâ€™re likely duplicates.

is the TypeScript function that derives these keys from the document content.
The keys should be deterministic (same content produces same keys) and sensitive to meaningful changes while ignoring non-meaningful differences like whitespace.
